*"2050500332" is silkscreened on the main board in the FCC photos. :"2050500351" is silkscreened on the main board in the user photos. *"2052500400" is silkscreened on the back of the wireless module. This device is basically a [[TP-LINK TL-WDR7500 v2.x]] (Archer C7R) :with 3 external and 3 internal antennas. Default settings are per ''TP-LINK'''s manual.
===Wikis=== *[http://wiki.openwrt.org/toh/tp-link/tl-wdr7500 ''TP-Link TL-WDR7500 / TP-Link Archer C7 AC1750'' on '''OpenWrt''' Wiki] :[https://lists.ath9k.org/pipermail/ath9k-devel/2013-June/011828.html Per ''sujith'' on ''ath9k-devel'', the card in the ''Archer C7'' is a '''CUS223 v1.0''']
===Reviews=== *[http://www.smallnetbuilder.com/wireless/wireless-reviews/32196-tp-link-archer-c7-ac1750-wireless-dual-band-gigabit-router-reviewed ''Reviewed'' on '''SmallNetBuilder'''] :"2050500351" is silkscreened on the board. :The Flash chip is noted as an 8MB ''[[Winbond]]'' W25Q64FV. :The 5GHz PAMs are noted as ''[[Skyworks]]'' (''SiGe'') SE5005L *[http://nl.hardware.info/reviews/4680/2/tp-link-archer-c7-review-80211ac-voor-een-schappelijke-prijs-qualcomm-in-plaats-van-broadcom ''Review'' on '''nl.hardware.info'''] :"2050500351" is silkscreened on the board. :The wireless module appears to be using QCA9880-AR1A ::[http://nl.hardware.info/nieuws/33842/cebit-twee-80211ac-ac1750-routers-bij-tp-link Their ''CeBIT'' article on the device] *[http://forums.overclockers.co.uk/showthread.php?p=24424655 ''Review by Locky'' on the '''Overclockers''' forums] :"2050500332" is silkscreened on the board. :v1.0 board (internal pictures), '''GTT''' capacitors, using: :[[QCA]] QCA9558-AT4A + QCA9880-AR1A + AR8327N-BL1A *[http://www.withoutthesarcasm.com/tp-link-archer-c7-ac1750-wireless-router-review/ ''Review'' on '''withoutthesarcasm.com'''] :OUI: 64:66:B3 *[http://www.hkepc.com/9324 On '''hkepc.com'''] :"2050500332" is silkscreened on the board. :OUI: F8:1A:67 *[https://www.microcontrollertips.com/teardown-inside-tp-link-archer-c7-wireless-router/ Teardown on '''MicrocontrollerTips'''] :"2050500351" is silkscreened on the board.
